The Firearms Control Amendment Bill 2021 has triggered heated debates. For members of the Shukokai Sport Shooting Club in Cape Town, they fear it may be the end of their sport. eNCA’s Monique Mortlock has the story. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Sport shooting could take a major hit if proposed changes to the firearms bill are passed. The Firearms Control Amendment Bill 2021 was published in the gazette last month. READ: Move to ban guns for self-defence The police ministry says the amendments are key to a safer South Africa. Changes to the 2015 Bill include prohibiting citizens from obtaining a gun license for self-defence. READ: SAPS questioned on shambles at Central Firearms Registry offices The public has until 4 July to submit comments on the draft bill. * eNCA’s Monique Mortlock reports.